1. docker info
2. sudo service docker start
3. sudo service docker status
4. The docker -idt command in Docker is used to run a container in detached mode 
with an interactive terminal. Here's a breakdown of the options:
-i: Keep STDIN open even if not attached (interactive mode).
-d: Run the container in detached mode (in the background).
-t: Allocate a pseudo-TTY (terminal).

5. sudo docker build -t myapp .
6. sudo docker run -p 8080:80 myapp
7. sudo docker stop <container id>
8. sudo docks ps 